<item>
            <title>[HTTPCORE-573] FileContentDecoder don&apos;t always enforce the maximum number of bytes to transfer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCORE-573</link>
                <project id="12310340" key="HTTPCORE">HttpComponents HttpCore</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The FileContentDecoder.transfer function has the &apos;count&apos; parameter indicating the maximum number of bytes to transfer.&lt;br/&gt;
 Implementations (LengthDelimitedDecoder and IdentityDecoder) don&apos;t respect this parameter when getting the data from the internal buffer: in practice the whole buffer content is transferred, thus the actual number of bytes transferred may exceed the maximum requested by caller.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the way data are read from the buffer can be limited, it is possible to respect the requested &apos;count&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
